The article applauds Congressman David Cicilline and the Congressional Equality Caucus for introducing the Equality Act in the House of Representatives. It urges Congress to pass this legislation, which aims to ensure that all individuals are treated with dignity and respect. The article highlights that LGBTQ+ Americans have been denied full equality for too long, and despite progress, discrimination still exists in many areas of society. The Equality Act seeks to provide federal civil rights protections based on sexual orientation and gender identity, specifically in housing, education, public services, and lending systems. The author also mentions signing an Executive Order on Preventing and Combating Discrimination on the Basis of Gender Identity or Sexual Orientation, directing agencies to enforce existing laws. The article concludes by emphasizing the need for Congress to pass the Equality Act to protect individuals from discrimination and fear based on their identity or whom they love.